## HTML Conversion Standards

**ALWAYS:**
- Auto-extract description from first paragraph (‚â§155 chars)
- Images: `<img src="../img/{name}" alt="{alt}" width="{w}" loading="lazy">`
- External links: `target="_blank" rel="noopener"`
- BEM naming, semantic HTML5 (h2/h3/strong/em/code/pre/ul/ol/figure)
- Paths: `../` (ES), `../../` (EN/PT)
- Generate distinct slugs per language (translate, don't duplicate)
- **Translate full content** for EN/PT versions (preserve code blocks, technical terms, formatting)
- **Code formatting:**
  - Inline: `<code>text</code>`
  - Blocks: `<pre class="c-post__prompt c-post__prompt--scroll"><code class="c-post__prompt-code">text</code></pre>`

**NEVER:**
- Use h1 in content body
- Omit `loading="lazy"` on images
- Use identical slugs across languages
- Skip content translation (EN/PT must be complete)
- Use plain `<pre><code>` for code blocks (requires BEM classes)